v:4 c:$ m:T05-loop-export role:dev x:serialization
gate: LOCKED

task: Serialize the recorded loop to a portable JSON artifact (DAWW3 ownable-jam on-ramp)

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/composables/useLoopRecorder.ts
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/components/JamControls.vue

depends: [T04-loop-recorder]

context: |
  This is the concrete step toward the DAWW3 vision: a quantized loop becomes a
  portable, signable artifact. NOT minting/on-chain (out of scope) — just a clean,
  deterministic serialization that a future mint/persist step can consume.

  Artifact shape (stable, versioned):
    interface JamLoopArtifact {
      v: 1
      createdAt: string          // ISO
      author: { peerId: string; name: string }
      tempo: { bpm: number; lengthBeats: number; division: number }
      scale: { divisions: number }     // from ScaleSystem
      instrument: string               // author's selected instrument
      notes: { note: number; velocity: number; startBeat: number; durBeats: number }[]
      // hashable: a stable JSON.stringify of the above (sorted keys) is the
      // canonical bytes a future on-chain step would hash/sign.
    }

steps:
  1. useLoopRecorder: add exportLoop(): JamLoopArtifact | null built from the
     current Loop + author (network.peerId/peerName) + ScaleSystem.divisions +
     selected instrument name.
  2. Add toCanonicalJSON(artifact): string with sorted keys (deterministic) so
     the same loop always serializes identically (future hash stability).
  3. Add a "download" action: serialize and trigger a Blob download
     (jam-loop-<timestamp>.json). Also log a one-line summary to the Event List.
  4. JamControls Loop section: add an "Export" button (enabled only when a loop
     exists). Existing styles.

note: |
  Leave a short code comment marking toCanonicalJSON's output as the future
  hash/sign input — this is the seam the DAWW3 monetization layer plugs into.

done:
  - With a recorded loop, Export produces a downloadable, deterministic JSON
  - Re-exporting the same loop yields byte-identical canonical JSON
  - Artifact includes tempo grid, scale, author, instrument, beat-relative notes
  - tsc --noEmit passes
